  <front>
   <head>To Mrs. CÆsar, at the Speaker's Lodgings at Bath.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">lately you acquitted me,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With  I din'd;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, in Return, (tho' grievous) thee</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">I resign'd.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis wise the happy Hour to seize;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">For, search the Nation round,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Such Peers, or Commoners, as these,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Where are they to be found?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Our Situation's chang'd you see:</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">(How Pleasures fleet away!)</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But Yesterday you envy'd me;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">I envy you To-day.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
